    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1836"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1836">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 767.70/441.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Morgenthau</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 37.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 17, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith in
                    duplicate, copy, with translation, of the Turco-Servian Treaty which was signed
                    by the plenipotentiaries of the respective countries on the 14th instant.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d1836fn1">Not printed. It ratifies the Treaty of London of May
                        30, 1913. (<hi rend="italic">See</hi>
                        <ref target="frus1913#pg_1309">For. Rel. 1913, p. 1309</ref>.)</note> In
                    addition to the treaty, I have the honor to transmit the letter exchanged by the
                    signatories on the subject of mosques in the ceded territories.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1836fn2">Not printed.</note> Diplomatic relations between Servia
                    and Turkey have been resumed and Mr. Georgevitch has been nominated Servian
                    Chargé d’Affaires.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. Morgenthau</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
